### Notes

*   ^ Just to be excruciatingly clear, the system, in its infinite wisdom, does not deem certain namespaces worthy of this particular brand of scrutiny. Pages residing in Category talk, Draft talk, File talk, Help talk, MediaWiki talk, Module talk, Portal talk, Talk, Template talk, User, User talk, and Wikipedia talk namespaces are, by design, excluded from these tracking categories. Consider it a small mercy, a quiet corner where even the algorithms fear to tread. Furthermore, any page with a name that, for some obscure reason, matches the patterns of '/[Ss]andbox', '/[Tt]estcases', '/[^/]*[Ll]og', or '/[Aa]rchive' is also granted immunity. These are the digital equivalent of 'do not disturb' signs, signaling that these pages are likely experimental, temporary, or historical, and thus not relevant to the current cleanup efforts. A rare instance of pragmatic exclusion, if I do say so myself.